Brazilian Stocks: Gol Linhas, Even, Rossi Advance; Tam Declines

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-03-18T21:12:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/brazilian-stocks-gol-linhas-even-rossi-advance-tam-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 1 percent to 66,879.89.    Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA (GOLL4)  (GOLL4 BS) gained 0.6
percent to 21.74 reais. Gol passed  Tam SA (TAMM4)  as  Brazil ’s market
leader in domestic flights, according to an e-mailed statement
from the country’s aviation authority.    Even Construtora e Incorporadora SA (EVEN3)  (EVEN3 BS) rose 1.2
percent to 8.15 reais and  Rossi Residencial SA (RSID3)  (RSID3 BS) jumped
2.3 percent to 14.01 reais. Even is in talks to sell control and
Rossi is the most likely buyer, newspaper  Valor Economico 
reported, without saying where it got the information. Even
denied the report, according to an e-mailed statement from an
outside public relations company.  Tam SA (TAMM4 BS) fell 3.8 percent to 31.85 reais, the
lowest since Aug. 12. A Chilean antitrust tribunal decided to
proceed with a review of its planned tie-up with Lan Airlines SA
to create Latin America’s largest carrier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  